gomodel:SYNGO_3947  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: SV2B immunoreactivity in immune-EM sections is present in glutamatergic but not GABAergic axon terminals. Immunoisolated SV preparations show SV2B co-IP with vGluT1/2 but not VGAT-SVs.\n\n-Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.\n\n19/01/2021 Dnyanada: PMID: 31959215 added to this annotation uses immunoEM data to demonstrate localisation of SV2 to synaptic vesicles. As the paper does not comment on which of the SV2 isoforms the antibody is specific for, it was added to the additional literature field for all SV2 CC annotations.. Experimental description: M&M: Adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (190-220 g; Charles River, Milan, Italy) were used." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3947" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

